rosy /ˈrəʊzɪ/

(rosier,rosiest) 

1. ADJ If you say that someone has a rosy face, you mean that they have pink cheeks and look very healthy. (面色) 红润的 

例： Bethan's round, rosy face seemed hardly to have aged at all. 贝森那张红润的圆脸看上去几乎一点儿也没有变老。 

2. ADJ If you say that a situation looks rosy or that the picture looks rosy , you mean that the situation seems likely to be good or successful. 乐观的 

例： The job prospects for those graduating in engineering are far less rosy now than they used to be. 那些工科毕业生的就业前景远不如以往那么乐观。

